Nigeria’s former Aviation Minister, Chief Femi Fani-Kayode has claimed that President Muhammadu Buhari’s bad luck caused the recent sack of Rex Tillerson from his position as United States Secretary of State. President Donald Trump on Tuesday, March 13, 2018, sacked Rex Tillerson as Secretary of State, replacing him with CIA Director Mike Pompeo. Buhari on Monday met behind closed doors with Tillerson during his official visit to Nigeria as US Secretary of State. He was fired moments later.    __________ Follow us on Twitter at @thesignalng Copyright 2018 SIGNAL. Permission to use portions of this article is granted provided appropriate credits are given to www.signalng.com and other relevant sources. The post Buhari’s Bad Luck Caused the Sack of Rex Tillerson – Fani-Kayode appeared first on SIGNAL. Do you have something awesome to share with the world? Click here to share Do you ever have any question about anything you wish to ask and get answer? Click here to ask Follow us on twitter @NigeriaTodayNG Also, Like us on facebook This post was syndicated from SIGNAL. Click here to read the full text on the original website.